Removed 600G and 500G modes of operation for the core OTN subsystem and replaced with two methods for configuring the use of the ODTUjk multiplexing resources: SDK managed allocation of the resources and user managed allocation of the resources. The SDK managed allocation offers the same non-blocking capacity as the previously defined modes. The user managed allocation supports additional non-blocking capacity when a HO OTN container contains LO signals of the same type.
